==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hippuric
<hw>Hip*pu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"i`ppos</grk> horse + <grk>o"y`ron</grk> urine: cf. F.
<ets>hippurique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>Obtained
from the urine of horses; <as>as, <ex>hippuric</ex> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hippuric acid</b></col>, <cd>a white crystalline
substance, containing nitrogen, present in the urine of herbivorous
animals, and in small quantity in human urine. By the action of acids,
it is decomposed into benzoic acid and glycocoll.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hippurite</ent>⟦br⟧
